		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Gadsden flag</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:252px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Gadsden_flag.svg" class="image" title="The Gadsden Flag"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d8/Gadsden_flag.svg/250px-Gadsden_flag.svg.png" width="250" height="167" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Gadsden_flag.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
The Gadsden Flag</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The <b>Gadsden flag</b> is a historical <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="/wiki/Flag" title="Flag">flag</a> with a <a href="/wiki/Yellow" title="Yellow">yellow</a> field depicting a <a href="/wiki/Rattlesnake" title="Rattlesnake">rattlesnake</a> coiled and ready to strike. Positioned below the snake is the legend "DONT TREAD ON ME" [<i><a href="/wiki/Sic" title="Sic">sic</a></i>]. The flag was designed by and is named after American general and statesman <a href="/wiki/Christopher_Gadsden" title="Christopher Gadsden">Christopher Gadsden</a>. It was also used by The United States Marine Corps as an early motto flag.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
